            "description": "Dataset-local second-pass Optuna screen for U-CaGNN. Without --dataset, the runner creates one independent study per core thesis dataset, so --trials N means target N compatible completed trials per dataset; existing compatible logical sampled_params count and are not rerun. The base grid is only a fallback. The parameters_by_dataset overrides are the active research grid: AmazonBook keeps the 0.004-0.005 LR / 5-3-2 basin while retaining 8-4 formal-run evidence; MovieLens keeps none/plateau schedules around 0.0004-0.005 with 2-to-3 layer branches; KuaiRec focuses on the 0.0002-0.0008 low-LR/lighter-fanout basin but keeps a small high-LR probe; KuaiRand focuses on dropout 0.15-0.30, plateau/cosine schedules, and 8-4 or 16-8 fanouts because the current best trials trade runtime for accuracy. This pass also tunes active causal branch-supervision weights and auxiliary schedule controls because those weights are thesis-owned rather than paper-fixed. The epoch cap is deliberately higher than the formal default, with fixed early stopping, so promising configurations can keep improving while weak ones stop without burning the full budget. Four-hop GNN depth remains excluded: current evidence does not justify extra over-smoothing and compute risk for the thesis budget.",
